    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - MISCELLANEOUS INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>MISCELLANEOUS INSTALLATION</title>
        <para>Refer to the appropriate sections of this publication for the proper installation procedures of the
            following:
        </para>
        <para>Oil, fuel and coolant filters</para>
        <para>Auto tensioner</para>
        <para>Belt</para>
        <para>ECM and Mounting Bracket, if equipped</para>
        <para>Valve Cover/Intake Manifold</para>
        <para>Road draft tube</para>
        <para>Cylinder head</para>
        <para>Fuel injectors</para>
        <para>Wiring harness</para>
        <para>Thermostat</para>
        <para>Oil level gauge and tube assembly</para>
        <para>Exhaust manifold</para>
        <para>Turbocharger</para>
        <para>Turbocharger supply and drain lines</para>
        <para>Coolant filter header</para>
        <para>Fuel filter header and fuel lines lines</para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>ADJUST THE VALVE LASH AS SPECIFIED IN SECTION 4 AND PRIME THE LUBRICATING SYSTEM AS SPECIFIED IN
                    SECTION 9.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
